This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with predicting user adoption in online social networks. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) as it involves analyzing social influence. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) as it deals with online behavior. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
